details.title: What is the Speaking test format?
details.description: The IELTS Speaking exam has three parts to it, and answering correctly is critical to receive a good result. So, here's a video that explains the IELTS Speaking test's structure.

details.title: Part 1 of Speaking
details.description: The examiner will ask 4-6 simple questions on familiar topics in section 1 of the Speaking examination. The examiner will most likely begin by introducing himself or herself and asking your name, followed by a request for you to prove your identity. This video has all the nuances of speaking part 1.

details.title: Part 2 of Speaking
details.description: Part 2 assesses your abilities to discuss a topic, generate ideas about a topic, and use appropriate language and grammar. This video will teach you all you need to know about speaking in part 2.

details.title: Part 3 of Speaking
details.description: The details of speaking part 3 are presented in this video. The examiner will continue on and ask you some follow-up questions once you finish the 'Cue Card/Candidate Task Card,' which is the second portion of the speaking examination.

details.title: How to answer Part 1
details.description: How long should my answers be? What topics would I be asked? Can I ask him questions? This video will address all such queries.

details.title: How to answer Part 2
details.description: Do you know what tense to use and what style to speak in when handed a cue card? Should you speak about a planned goal and an achieved goal in the same manner? To address all those queries, here is a video on how to form your speaking part 2 answers.

details.title: How to answer Part 3
details.description: A 2-way discussion will certainly be one of the most daunting parts of the speaking examination. You will have to use the right tone and structure to express your views and opinions. This video will tell you how to do all of that and more.

details.title: Linking words in IELTS Speaking
details.description: How will the examiner know the relation between your sentences? Using the right words to exhibit your command over the language is key when joining sentences. Watch on and find out more about linking words.

details.title: How to maintain fluency in Speaking
details.description: Keeping the pace and not stuttering in between speaking is crucial to a good score. Spending time thinking of the right words to use will also not help your cause. Watch this video to find out how you can improve your score in the FC criteria of the speaking assessment.

details.title: Speaking Part 3- Opinion Question type
details.description: Do you know how to present your opinions? What would you say if the examiner wants your take on a topic? Watch carefully as this video will tell you exactly what to do.

details.title: Speaking Part 3- Evaluate Question type
details.description: How you assess a topic is something of a curiosity of everyone. Using the right vocabulary and other details of the language will certainly help you get a proper score. This video will discuss how to present your evaluations on a topic.

details.title: Speaking Part 3- Future Question type
details.description: Can you speak about an event that has not happened yet? Do you know what tenses should be used? This video will speak about how to present your predictions.

details.title: Speaking Part 3- Cause & Effect Question type
details.description: Can you speak about an event that has not happened yet? Do you know what tenses should be used? This video will speak about how to present your predictions.

details.title: Speaking Part 3- Hypothetical Question type
details.description: What if you are asked about something that you have no clue of or are pretty sure does not exist? Per say, Aliens? What do you answer with? No clue? That’s alright. Have a look at this video and find out!

details.title: Speaking Part 3- Compare & Contrast Question type
details.description: Questions that ask you to find parallels between one time frame and another time frame are quite common. Let’s find out how they are answered in this video.

details.title: Speaking Part 3- Talking about Past Question type
details.description: Childhood seems to be a topic of particular interest to IELTS examiners. Well childhood is in the past! So would you be able to answer a question relating to the past in an effective and acceptable manner? That is the topic of this video. Have a look!

details.title: Speaking Part 3- Talking about Frequency Question type
details.description:
Speaking Part 3- Talking about Frequency Question Type
How frequently an activity is done in your country is a common question that you might get. Check this video to see how to answer such questions.

details.title: IELTS Speaking Assessment Criteria
details.description: Examiners are interested in certain things in your speech. Fluency and pronunciations happen to be a few of them. Do you know what other aspects are looked at when you speak? Find out in this video.
